Product WAREHOUSE Maintenance

 

This Component is used to attach product for warehouse.

At the initial load screen all available Products will be listed in the grid.

 

1st Screen

 

v  By expanding the Selection Criteria, User will be able to filter Products accordingly.

Selection could be based onProduct Classification. Example-Product Type, Product Category, Team Code, Supplier Code, Product Class.

 

 

 

v  There are following Options associated with the Main screen.

 

Add New Product Warehouse to the System

  Click New Button

 

Load specific Product attached for warehouses in the System

  Select Product Load Button

 

Exit from Product WarehouseMaintenance

  Click Exit Button

 

 

v  In the Product Warehouse Creation Process following fields are mandatory.

  Product Code

  Warehouse Code

 

Creating a new product warehouse

  User can create a new Product Warehouseby clicking the New button.

 

 

  When clicking the new button, following interface appears and the user will be able to enter the Product Warehouse related details.

 

2nd Screen

  Product Code: Allows the user to select particular Product and description through the prompt.

  Warehouse Code: Allows selecting the warehouse which the Product belongs to.

  Location Code: Allows the user to select particular location code and the description through the prompt.

  Preferred Supplier: Allows selecting the Supplier Code and Description through the prompt.

Those Product Code, Warehouse Code, location code and Preferred Supplier combinations are unique. It cannot be duplicated.

  Rest of the fields will allow to maintaining the stock details, Such as Re-Order level, Min Stock Level, Max Stock Level, Economic Order Quantity and etc

 

After entering relevant details, user can click OK to save the Product Warehouse details or Cancel to discard the specifications and return to the 1st Screen.

 

 

LoadingProduct Warehouse

 

  User can View the all attached warehouse for a particular Product by clicking the Load button.

 

When clicking the Load button, following interface appears.

 

3rd Screen

v  There are following Options associated with the Load screen.

 

Edit a Product Warehouse to the System

  Click Edit Button

Exit from Product Warehouse Load Screen

  Click Cancel Button

 

EditProduct Warehouse

  User can edit certain data by clicking the Edit button or go back to the 1stscreen by clicking Cancel button.

 

When clicking the Edit button, following interface appears.

 

4th Screen

 

The user can change all attributes except the Product Code and Warehouse Code.User can edit the relevant fields and click OK button to save or click Cancel button to move back to the 3rdScreen.

 

 

 

 

 

  Attach the Product warehouse accordingly since it these products will be loaded for certain transactions.

 

 

 

  Do not attach unwanted warehouse to aProduct.
